only val3 gets stored

If you have a gadget that has only 'hidden' user prefs, then saving these prefs wont get persisted to the server.

This is because the prefs queuing function (setUserPref) is only bound to the iframe, if the gadget if isEditable().  isEditable() is implemented like this:
{code}
return !!(this.getLayoutManager().isWritable() && this.hasNonHiddenUserPrefs);   
{code}

So to re-produce the problem:
* Create a gadget spec with hidden user prefs *only*
* Call prefs.set() on one of those prefs

The prefs wont get POSTed to the server.

